: 1773
Name: Abraham
Translation - Muhammad Tahir-ul-Qadri: Have you not seen how Allah sets forth an example: a good word is like a good tree? Its root is firm (in the earth) and its branches reach into the sky.
Translation - Arthur J: Hast thou not seen how God has struck a similitude? A good word is as a good tree -- its roots are firm, and its branches are in heaven;
Tafaseer - Tafsir al-Jalalayn: Have you not seen observed how God has struck a similitude? mathalan is substituted by the following words kalimatan tayyibatan a goodly saying which is ‘there is no god but God’ is as a goodly tree a palm tree its root set firm in the ground and its shoots its branches are in heaven;
Surah : Ayat: 14:24

